Class CsvConversionUtil

java.lang.Object
org.techbd.util.CsvConversionUtil
public class CsvConversionUtil extends Object
Utility class for converting CSV data into domain-specific models grouped by patient MR ID.

      public static Map<String,List<org.techbd.model.csv.DemographicData>> convertCsvStringToDemographicData(String csvData)
      Converts a CSV string into a map of demographic data grouped by `patientMrIdValue`.
      Parameters:
      csvData - the CSV data as a string
      Returns:
      a map where the key is the patient MR ID value and the value is the list of demographic data with that ID
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs during reading or parsing the CSV

    • convertCsvStringToObjectMap

      public static <T> Map<String,List<T>> convertCsvStringToObjectMap(String csvData, Class<T> clazz, char separator, String fieldName) throws IOException
      Converts a CSV string into a list of objects of the specified class type and groups them by a specified field.
      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the objects in the list
      Parameters:
      csvData - the CSV data as a string
      clazz - the class of the objects to convert to
      separator - the character used as the CSV separator
      fieldName - the field name to group by (e.g., "patientMrIdValue" or "encounterId")
      Returns:
      a map where the key is the field value (e.g., patient MR ID or encounter ID) and the value is the list of objects with that value
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs during reading or parsing the CSV
